6. Bug-Fix History
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Session: 2026-04-18  (commit cf73738)

  BUG-01 [C++] Loop explosion in recursive walk
    Symptom : instagram.com / facebook.com returned "Resolution failed"
    Root    : walk() had no visited-server guard; revisiting the same
              nameserver caused infinite delegation loops
    Fix     : Added O(n) visited check before pushing ns_ip to path

  BUG-02 [C++] CNAME chain restarted from a random root every time
    Symptom : Multi-hop CNAME domains (CDN-heavy: instagram, facebook)
              failed because restarting from root lost the delegation context
    Fix     : On CNAME, first try the current authoritative NS; if that
              fails, try 3 random roots (not all 13)

  BUG-03 [C++] Glue-less NS resolution polluted the main path vector
    Symptom : resolve_ns_name() passed the shared `path` vector to walk(),
              so NS hostname lookups added many entries, triggering the
              MAX_REFERRALS=30 limit and false loop-detection hits
    Fix     : resolve_ns_name() now uses its own local std::vector<string>
              per attempt; main resolution path is untouched

  BUG-04 [C++] Per-hop UDP timeout too high during NS fan-out
    Symptom : With 3 s/hop × many glue-less NS lookups the 15 s Flask
              timeout was regularly exceeded
    Fix     : Reduced per-hop UDP timeout from implicit 3 s to 2 s;
              increased Flask RESOLVER_TIMEOUT from 15 s to 30 s

  BUG-05 [C++] Truncated UDP responses not retried via TCP in walk()
    Symptom : Responses with TC bit set were silently dropped
    Fix     : Explicit TC check in walk(); retry via send_tcp() if set

  BUG-06 [Python] No fallback when C++ walk fails
    Symptom : Domains with complex CDN CNAME chains returned 503/404
              even when 8.8.8.8 could answer in <5 ms
    Fix     : Added fallback_resolve() — raw UDP to 8.8.8.8 with full
              RFC 1035 pointer decompression; called on both timeout
              (RuntimeError) and success=False response from C++

